# =====================================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY REMINDERS
# =====================================================

# NEVER commit:
# - API keys or tokens
# - Database passwords
# - SSL certificates
# - SSH keys
# - Service account files
# - Any .env files except .env.example

# If you accidentally commit sensitive data:
# 1. Remove it from the repository immediately
# 2. Revoke/regenerate the exposed credentials
# 3. Consider using git-filter-branch or BFG Repo-Cleaner
# 4. Force push the cleaned history